25|$|Carter Glass (January 4, 1858 – May 28, 1946) was a {{newspaper}} publisher and Democratic politician from Lynchburg, Virginia. He represented Virginia {{in both houses}} of Congress and served as the United States Secretary of the Treasury under President Woodrow Wilson. He {{played a major role in}} the establishment of the U.S. financial regulatory system, helping to establish the Federal Reserve System and the <b>Federal</b> <b>Deposit</b> <b>Insurance</b> Corporation.|$|E
